<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-525-782  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 525 782.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer-Aided Engineering  May 1990 v9 n5 p24(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Workstation users want lower prices.andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>An Oct 1989 survey by Strategic Focus, a market research andconsulting firm, shows that workstation users find price to be theprimary reason for changing vendors.andP;  Reliability and support arelisted as the reasons for switching vendors by only 7 percent ofthe respondents.andP;  Better networking capabilities would cause 12percent to switch.andP;  The results show 61 percent expect to be in anintegrated network within two years.andP;  Of the respondents insoftware development, 45 percent consider price first withsoftware portability at 43 percent and reliability at 35 percent.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SurveyWorkstationsPrice.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Top reasons for switching vendors. (graph)Computing environment. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>